250 g Ground Beef
113 g Mirepoix
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
170 g Spaghetti
30 g Capers
56 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tsp Chili Flakes
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

When water is boiling, add spaghetti. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10-12 min.
Drain and return spaghetti to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, line a plate with paper towels.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
Drain and rinse capers, then pat dry with paper towels.
When the pan is hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) oil, then capers. Fry until crispy, 3-4 min.
Remove with a slotted spoon to the prepared plate.

Add mirepoix to the same pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies start to soften, 1-2 min.
Add beef, Zesty Garlic Blend and garlic puree. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 3-4 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.

Add crushed tomatoes and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to beef mixture. Cook, stirring occasionally, until well combined, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter into sauce, until melted. Remove from heat.
Add sauce into the pot with spaghetti. Add spinach, then stir until spinach is wilted, 1 min.

Divide pasta between bowls.
Top with Parmesan cheese, fried capers and as much chili flakes as desired.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**